content.description: Just a nice long traverse right next to the parking lot of Qdoba in Unversity Ave.   Good rock, nice feet, plus food next door.
content.protection: Theres grass but grab a crashpad
content.location: If you go to Qdoba on Unversity Ave.  (2741 University ave) its on the other side of the parking lot.  Youll see it as you drive in.

content.description: Just to left of Qdoba wall, this wall packs in some great edges, crimps, and i even found jugs and underclings.  This would be super fun.
content.location: Again next to Qdoba (2741 University Ave)

content.description: It's a pretty nice and easy warm-up set to set you up for the Burrito Wall boulder 3 blocks down. The first move is a mantel up a concrete platform followed by a brick wall with aided apparatus. The last move is the crux with a 2 ft reach and a hop over the garden plaza above.
content.protection: a 6 packs of beer and 2 bls of beef, cause there's a community grill and nice table set up where you top off.
content.location: Behind Lombardino's restaurant. At the corner of University and Highland ave.

content.description: Other buildings around madison other than the Campus area to get your climb on.
